{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864319564,"sessionID":"ses_2863d152fffe0X4eNRN7W0rgq7","part":{"id":"prt_d79c3082e001sHX5QiTOBOX5RT","messageID":"msg_d79c2ebbe001W0i6docvco5TXd","sessionID":"ses_2863d152fffe0X4eNRN7W0rgq7","type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"toolu_tool-f1f6ce9f92e04d388c1310546a91de4f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"PicoD.*JWT|JWT.*middleware"},"output":"Found 36 matches\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 Tasks\n  Line 7: | AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/design.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 Design\n  Line 7: | AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n  Line 13: PicoD JWT 中间件提供基于 RSA 公钥的 JWT token 验证机制，用于保护 PicoD 的 `/api/*` 端点。该中间件从环境变量加载公钥，验证请求中的 Bearer token，并将验证结果传递给后续处理器。\n  Line 306: ├── auth.go            # AuthManager, JWT validation middleware\n  Line 405: - `pkg/router/middleware/auth.go` — Router JWT middleware (reference implementation)\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/.sdd_prompt.md:\n  Line 3: AR: AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 1: # Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n  Line 11: Implement a dedicated JWT authentication middleware for PicoD that provides secure RS256 token validation, runtime public key management for key rotation, and request body size limiting. This middleware ensures that all PicoD API endpoints (except health check) require valid JWT tokens issued by the Router, protecting sandbox pods from unauthorized access.\n  Line 116: The system SHALL implement JWT authentication middleware with Bearer token extraction.\n  Line 355: The system SHALL provide comprehensive test coverage for JWT middleware functionality.\n  Line 448: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Extend | Test coverage for JWT middleware, key rotation, PEM validation |\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/proposal.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 Proposal\n  Line 5: Implement a dedicated JWT authentication middleware for PicoD that provides secure RS256 token validation, runtime public key management for key rotation, and request body size limiting. This middleware ensures that all PicoD API endpoints (except health check) require valid JWT tokens issued by the Router, protecting sandbox pods from unauthorized access.\n  Line 7: **Current State**: JWT authentication was initially implemented as part of AR-015 within `pkg/picod/auth.go`. The implementation provides basic RS256 validation, public key loading from environment, and a Gin middleware function. However, the component lacks dedicated documentation, clear separation of concerns, and explicit support for key rotation scenarios.\n  Line 9: **Target State**: Well-documented JWT middleware component with:\n  Line 24: | `pkg/picod/auth.go` (document) | Document existing AuthManager, public key loading, JWT middleware implementation |\n  Line 152: **Decision**: Rejected. PicoD runs inside sandbox without direct kubelet access. Router-mediated JWT is more suitable for session-based auth.\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/spec.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n  Line 7: | AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/design.md:\n  Line 13: PicoD File Management API provides secure file operations within sandbox pods. It exposes REST endpoints for uploading, listing, and downloading files with workspace jail enforcement, path traversal protection, Base64/multipart upload support, and RS256 JWT authentication. The file API enables AI agents and code interpreters to manage workspace files safely within the sandbox boundary.\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 572: - AND all routes SHALL use existing JWT auth middleware\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md:\n  Line 333:    - All under `/api` with existing JWT auth middleware\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/design.md:\n  Line 13: PicoD (Pico Daemon) is an HTTP daemon that runs inside sandbox pods to provide secure command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail. It exposes REST APIs protected by RS256 JWT authentication, enabling AI agents and code interpreters to execute shell commands and manage workspace files with timeout control, path traversal protection, and workspace jail enforcement.\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 11: Define the PicoD (Pico Daemon) HTTP daemon that runs inside sandbox pods to provide secure command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail. PicoD exposes REST APIs protected by RS256 JWT authentication, enabling AI agents and code interpreters to execute shell commands and manage workspace files with timeout control, path traversal protection, and workspace jail enforcement.\n  Line 147: ### Requirement: JWT authentication middleware\n  Line 149: The system SHALL implement JWT authentication middleware with RS256 validation.\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md:\n  Line 5: Implement PicoD (Pico Daemon), an HTTP daemon that runs inside sandbox pods to provide secure command execution and file management within a configurable workspace jail. This enables AI agents and code interpreters to execute shell commands and manage workspace files through a JWT-protected REST API.\n  Line 26: | `pkg/picod/auth.go` | `AuthManager` struct, RSA public key loading from PEM, JWT middleware with MaxBytesReader |\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md:\n  Line 399: | `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | Modified | Add JWT middleware tests |\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/design.md:\n  Line 113: | `JWTAuthMiddleware` | Token verification middleware (future) | `JWTManager` |\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 11: Define the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that resolves session IDs from request headers, creates sandboxes via Workload Manager, forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`, generates RS256-signed JWT tokens, updates session activity timestamps, and limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware.\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/code-execution/design.md:\n  Line 178: ## JWT middleware (`AuthManager`)\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/code-execution/spec.md:\n  Line 5: PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail, manages workspace files, and exposes a health endpoint with JWT (RSA)–protected APIs.\n  Line 141: The system SHALL expose `GET /health` without JWT middleware and respond HTTP 200 with JSON including `status`, `service`, `version`, and `uptime`.","metadata":{"matches":36,"truncated":false},"title":"PicoD.*JWT|JWT.*middleware","time":{"start":177586431