{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864333013,"sessionID":"ses_2863d152fffe0X4eNRN7W0rgq7","part":{"id":"prt_d79c33ebb0017nJkEsd3G19jYE","messageID":"msg_d79c32b600016qmsZuDi3rYTiF","sessionID":"ses_2863d152fffe0X4eNRN7W0rgq7","type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"toolu_tool-a86e305e32644bb4a7db40212260400a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"pkg/picod/**/*.go"},"output":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/auth_test.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/picod_test.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/doc.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/execute.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/files.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/auth.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/sanitize.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/server.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/health.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/config.go","metadata":{"count":10,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z","time":{"start":1775864332996,"end":1775864333011}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864333020,"sessionID":"ses_2863d152fffe0X4eNRN7W0rgq7","part":{"id":"prt_d79c342a8001D01ljjHU0f6mve","messageID":"msg_d79c32b600016qmsZuDi3rYTiF","sessionID":"ses_2863d152fffe0X4eNRN7W0rgq7","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9366f32202734be4a19572375027d924","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Implement a dedicated JWT authentication middleware for PicoD that provides secure RS256 token validation, runtime public key management for key rotation, and request body size limiting. This middleware ensures that all PicoD API endpoints (except health check) require valid JWT tokens issued by the Router, protecting sandbox pods from unauthorized access.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: AuthManager type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `AuthManager` for RSA JWT authentication with thread-safe public key storage.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: AuthManager struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `AuthManager` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` for RSA public key\n26:   - `mutex sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe public key access\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AuthManager thread-safe storage\n29: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n30: - **WHEN** accessing publicKey concurrently\n31: - **THEN** read operations SHALL use `mutex.RLock()` / `mutex.RUnlock()`\n32: - AND write operations SHALL use `mutex.Lock()` / `mutex.Unlock()`\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ### Requirement: Public key environment variable\n37: \n38: The system SHALL define constant for public key environment variable name.\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: PublicKeyEnvVar constant\n41: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n42: - **WHEN** reading constants\n43: - **THEN** `PublicKeyEnvVar` SHALL be `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: MaxBodySize constant\n46: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n47: - **WHEN** reading constants\n48: - **THEN** `MaxBodySize` SHALL be `32 << 20` (32 MiB)\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ### Requirement: NewAuthManager constructor\n53: \n54: The system SHALL implement `NewAuthManager` constructor for AuthManager initialization.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: NewAuthManager initialization\n57: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n58: - **WHEN** calling `NewAuthManager()`\n59: - **THEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` SHALL be called\n60: - AND `publicKey` SHALL be set from PEM public key\n61: - AND `AuthManager` SHALL be returned with initialized publicKey\n62: - AND error SHALL be returned if env var is missing\n63: - AND error SHALL be returned if PEM decode fails\n64: - AND error SHALL be returned if PKIX parse fails\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: NewAuthManager startup fatal handling\n67: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n68: - **WHEN** `NewAuthManager()` returns error\n69: - **THEN** `NewServer` SHALL return error with wrapped message\n70: - AND caller (`cmd/picod/main.go`) SHALL call `klog.Fatalf` on failure\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ### Requirement: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv function\n75: \n76: The system SHALL implement public key loading from environment variable with PKIX format validation.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv environment read\n79: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n80: - **WHEN** loading public key\n81: - **THEN** `os.Getenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)` SHALL be called\n82: - AND `strings.TrimSpace()` SHALL remove leading/trailing whitespace\n83: - AND error SHALL be returned if env var is empty\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv PEM decode\n86: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n87: - **WHEN** decoding PEM block\n88: - **THEN** `pem.Decode([]byte(pemKey))` SHALL be called\n89: - AND error SHALL be returned if block is nil (invalid PEM)\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv PEM block type validation\n92: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n93: - **WHEN** validating PEM block type\n94: - **THEN** `block.Type` SHALL be `\"PUBLIC KEY\"` (PKIX format)\n95: - AND error SHALL be returned if block type is not `\"PUBLIC KEY\"`\n96: - AND PKCS#1 format (`\"RSA PUBLIC KEY\"` block type) SHALL be rejected\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv PKIX parsing\n99: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n100: - **WHEN** parsing public key bytes\n101: - **THEN** `x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)` SHALL be called\n102: - AND error SHALL be returned if PKIX parse fails\n103: - AND result SHALL be type-asserted to `*rsa.PublicKey`\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv RSA validation\n106: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n107: - **WHEN** validating key type\n108: - **THEN** type assertion `pub.(*rsa.PublicKey)` SHALL be performed\n109: - AND error SHALL be returned if key is not RSA\n110: - AND non-RSA public keys (ECDSA, DSA, Ed25519) SHALL be rejected\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ### Requirement: AuthMiddleware Bearer token extraction\n115: \n116: The system SHALL implement JWT authentication middleware with Bearer token extraction.\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware Authorization header extraction\n119: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n120: - **WHEN** processing request with `Authorization` header\n121: - **THEN** header SHALL be extracted via `c.GetHeader(\"Authorization\")`\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware missing Authorization header\n124: - **GIVEN** request without `Authorization` header\n125: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware processes request\n126: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n127: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"missing authorization header\"}`\n128: - AND `c.Abort()` SHALL be called\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware Bearer prefix validation\n131: - **GIVEN** request with `Authorization` header\n132: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware validates format\n133: - **THEN** `strings.HasPrefix(authHeader, \"Bearer \")` SHALL be checked\n134: - AND HTTP `401` SHALL be returned if prefix missing\n135: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid token format\"}`\n136: - AND `c.Abort()` SHALL be called\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware token string extraction\n139: - **GIVEN** valid `Authorization` header format\n140: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware extracts token\n141: - **THEN** `strings.TrimPrefix(authHeader, \"Bearer \")` SHALL strip prefix\n142: - AND result SHALL be token string for JWT parsing\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ### Requirement: AuthMiddleware RSA signing method validation\n147: \n148: The system SHALL validate JWT signing method is RSA to prevent algorithm substitution attacks.\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware public key read lock\n151: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n152: - **WHEN** accessing publicKey for validation\n153: - **THEN** `a.mutex.RLock()` SHALL acquire read lock\n154: - AND `pubKey := a.publicKey` SHALL read current key\n155: - AND `a.mutex.RUnlock()` SHALL release lock before parsing\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware RSA method type assertion\n158: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n159: - **WHEN** JWT keyFunc validates signing method\n160: - **THEN** `token.Method` SHALL be type-asserted to `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`\n161: - AND assertion success SHALL return `pubKey` for validation\n162: - AND assertion failure SHALL return error `\"invalid signing method\"`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware HS256 attack prevention\n165: - **GIVEN** JWT token signed with HS256 (symmetric) algorithm\n166: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware parses token\n167: - **THEN** signing method SHALL be detected as non-RSA\n168: - AND HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n169: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid signing method\"}`\n170: - AND `c.Abort()` SHALL be called\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware RSA algorithms acceptance\n173: - **GIVEN** JWT token signed with RS256, RS384, or RS512\n174: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware parses token\n175: - **THEN** signing method SHALL be accepted as RSA\n176: - AND token SHALL be validated with public key\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ### Requirement: AuthMiddleware JWT claim validation\n181: \n182: The system SHALL validate JWT claims with expiration, issued-at, and leeway options.\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware expiration required\n185: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n186: - **WHEN** parsing JWT\n187: - **THEN** `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()` SHALL be applied\n188: - AND tokens without `exp` claim SHALL be rejected\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware issued-at required\n191: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n192: - **WHEN** parsing JWT\n193: - **THEN** `jwt.WithIssuedAt()` SHALL be applied\n194: - AND tokens without `iat` claim SHALL be rejected\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware leeway tolerance\n197: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n198: - **WHEN** parsing JWT\n199: - **THEN** `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)` SHALL be applied\n200: - AND clock skew up to 1 minute SHALL be tolerated\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware expired token handling\n203: - **GIVEN** JWT token with expired `exp` claim\n204: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware validates token\n205: - **THEN** `jwt.ErrTokenExpired` SHALL be detected via `errors.Is`\n206: - AND HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n207: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"token is expired\"}`\n208: - AND `c.Abort()` SHALL be called\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware invalid signature handling\n211: - **GIVEN** JWT token with invalid signature\n212: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware validates token\n213: - **THEN** `jwt.ErrTokenSignatureInvalid` SHALL be detected via `errors.Is`\n214: - AND HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n215: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid signature\"}`\n216: - AND `c.Abort()` SHALL be called\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware generic error handling\n219: - **GIVEN** JWT validation failure with unrecognized error\n220: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware validates token\n221: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n222: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": err.Error()}` (original error message)\n223: - AND `c.Abort()` SHALL be called\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ### Requirement: AuthMiddleware request body size limiting\n228: \n229: The system SHALL apply request body size limit after successful JWT validation.\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware MaxBytesReader application\n232: - **GIVEN** valid JWT token\n233: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware completes validation\n234: - **THEN** `http.MaxBytesReader(c.Writer, c.Request.Body, MaxBodySize)` SHALL be applied\n235: - AND `MaxBodySize` SHALL be `32 << 20` (32 MiB)\n236: - AND request body exceeding limit SHALL be rejected\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: AuthMiddleware proceed to handler\n239: - **GIVEN** valid JWT token and successful validation\n240: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware completes\n241: - **THEN** `c.Next()` SHALL be called\n242: - AND request SHALL proceed to handler\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ### Requirement: Key rotation support\n247: \n248: The system SHALL provide runtime public key rotation support via SetPublicKey and GetPublicKey methods.\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: SetPublicKey thread-safe update\n251: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n252: - **WHEN** calling `SetPublicKey(key *rsa.PublicKey)`\n253: - **THEN** `a.mutex.Lock()` SHALL acquire write lock\n254: - AND `a.publicKey = key` SHALL update public key\n255: - AND `a.mutex.Unlock()` SHALL release lock\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: GetPublicKey thread-safe read\n258: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/auth.go`\n259: - **WHEN** calling `GetPublicKey()`\n260: - **THEN** `a.mutex.RLock()` SHALL acquire read lock\n261: - AND `defer a.mutex.RUnlock()` SHALL ensure release\n262: - AND `a.publicKey` SHALL be returned\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Key rotation during active requests\n265: - **GIVEN** concurrent requests and SetPublicKey call\n266: - **WHEN** key rotation occurs\n267: - **THEN** existing request validation SHALL complete with old key (read lock held)\n268: - AND subsequent requests SHALL use new key\n269: - AND no request SHALL fail due to key rotation race\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: Router key rotation coordination\n272: - **GIVEN** Router generates new key pair\n273: - **WHEN** Workload Manager pushes new public key\n274: - **THEN** `SetPublicKey()` SHALL be called on AuthManager\n275: - AND PicoD SHALL validate new tokens with new public key\n276: - AND service restart SHALL NOT be required\n277: \n278: ---\n279: \n280: ### Requirement: Server integration\n281: \n282: The system SHALL integrate AuthManager into PicoD server with middleware registration.\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: Server AuthManager field\n285: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n286: - **WHEN** reading the `Server` struct\n287: - **THEN** `authManager *AuthManager` SHALL be present\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: NewServer AuthManager initialization\n290: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n291: - **WHEN** calling `NewServer(config)`\n292: - **THEN** `NewAuthManager()` SHALL be called\n293: - AND `authManager` SHALL be set in Server\n294: - AND error SHALL be returned if AuthManager creation fails\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: API route group middleware registration\n297: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n298: - **WHEN** registering `/api` route group\n299: - **THEN** `api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())` SHALL apply middleware\n300: - AND all routes under `/api` SHALL require JWT authentication\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: Health endpoint authentication bypass\n303: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n304: - **WHEN** registering routes\n305: - **THEN** `/health` SHALL be registered directly on `engine` (not `/api` group)\n306: - AND `/health` SHALL NOT require JWT authentication\n307: - AND unauthenticated health check SHALL be available\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ### Requirement: Error handling\n312: \n313: The system SHALL handle JWT authentication errors with appropriate HTTP status codes and messages.\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Missing Authorization header error\n316: - **GIVEN** request without Authorization header\n317: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware rejects request\n318: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n319: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"missing authorization header\"}`\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: Invalid token format error\n322: - **GIVEN** Authorization header without Bearer prefix\n323: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware rejects request\n324: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n325: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid token format\"}`\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Invalid signing method error\n328: - **GIVEN** JWT signed with non-RSA algorithm\n329: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware rejects request\n330: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n331: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid signing method\"}`\n332: \n333: #### Scenario: Expired token error\n334: - **GIVEN** JWT with expired exp claim\n335: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware rejects request\n336: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n337: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"token is expired\"}`\n338: \n339: #### Scenario: Invalid signature error\n340: - **GIVEN** JWT with signature mismatch\n341: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware rejects request\n342: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n343: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid signature\"}`\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Invalid token error\n346: - **GIVEN** JWT validation failure with token.Valid false\n347: - **WHEN** AuthMiddleware rejects request\n348: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n349: - AND body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"invalid token\"}`\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ### Requirement: Test coverage\n354: \n355: The system SHALL provide comprehensive test coverage for JWT middleware functionality.\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Test missing authorization header\n358: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n359: - **WHEN** testing AuthMiddleware without Authorization header\n360: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n361: - AND error message SHALL be `\"missing authorization header\"`\n362: \n363: #### Scenario: Test invalid token format\n364: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n365: - **WHEN** testing AuthMiddleware with malformed Authorization header\n366: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n367: - AND error message SHALL be `\"invalid token format\"`\n368: \n369: #### Scenario: Test expired token\n370: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n371: - **WHEN** testing AuthMiddleware with expired JWT\n372: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n373: - AND error message SHALL be `\"token is expired\"`\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: Test invalid signature\n376: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n377: - **WHEN** testing AuthMiddleware with wrong signature\n378: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n379: - AND error message SHALL be `\"invalid signature\"`\n380: \n381: #### Scenario: Test HS256 rejection\n382: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n383: - **WHEN** testing AuthMiddleware with HS256-signed JWT\n384: - **THEN** HTTP `401` SHALL be returned\n385: - AND error message SHALL be `\"invalid signing method\"`\n386: \n387: #### Scenario: Test valid RS256 token\n388: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n389: - **WHEN** testing AuthMiddleware with valid RS256 JWT\n390: - **THEN** request SHALL proceed (c.Next called)\n391: - AND handler SHALL be invoked\n392: \n393: #### Scenario: Test key rotation\n394: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n395: - **WHEN** testing SetPublicKey with new key\n396: - **THEN** subsequent requests SHALL validate with new key\n397: - AND old-key-signed tokens SHALL be rejected\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: Test PEM format validation\n400: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n401: - **WHEN** testing LoadPublicKeyFromEnv with PKCS#1 PEM\n402: - **THEN** error SHALL be returned\n403: - AND error message SHALL indicate expected PUBLIC KEY block\n404: \n405: #### Scenario: Test environment variable missing\n406: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n407: - **WHEN** testing LoadPublicKeyFromEnv with empty env var\n408: - **THEN** error SHALL be returned\n409: - AND error message SHALL indicate environment variable not set\n410: \n411: #### Scenario: Test concurrent key access\n412: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n413: - **WHEN** testing concurrent SetPublicKey and GetPublicKey calls\n414: - **THEN** no race condition SHALL occur\n415: - AND mutex SHALL protect concurrent access\n416: \n417: ---\n418: \n419: ## Constants Summary\n420: \n421: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n422: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n423: | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | `auth.go` | Env var for PEM public key |\n424: | `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` | `auth.go` | Request body size limit (32 MiB) |\n425: \n426: ---\n427: \n428: ## Dependencies Summary\n429: \n430: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n431: |---------|---------|---------|\n432: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10+ | Gin middleware pattern; `gin.HandlerFunc`, `gin.Context` |\n433: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2+ | JWT parsing; RSA signing method validation, claim options |\n434: | `crypto/rsa` | Standard | RSA public key type |\n435: | `crypto/x509` | Standard | PKIX public key parsing |\n436: | `encoding/pem` | Standard | PEM block decoding |\n437: | `sync` | Standard | `sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe key storage |\n438: | `net/http` | Standard | `http.MaxBytesReader` for body limiting |\n439: \n440: ---\n441: \n442: ## File Changes Summary\n443: \n444: | File | Action | Description |\n445: |------|--------|-------------|\n446: | `pkg/picod/auth.go` | Document | `AuthManager`, `NewAuthManager`, `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv`, `AuthMiddleware`, `SetPublicKey`, `GetPublicKey` |\n447: | `pkg/picod/server.go` | Document | AuthManager integration, middleware registration |\n448: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Extend | Test coverage for JWT middleware, key rotation, PEM validation |\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ## References\n453: \n454: - `changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md` — Original PicoD implementation\n455: - `pkg/router/jwt.go` — Router JWT issuance (key pair generation)\n456: - [github.com/golang-jwt/jwt](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt)\n457: - [JWT Best Practices RFC 8725](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8725)\n\n(End of file - total 457 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement a dedicated JWT authentication middleware for PicoD that provides secure RS256 token validation, runtime public key management for key rotation, and request body size limiting. This middleware ensures that all PicoD API endpoints (except health check) require valid JWT tokens issued by the Router, protecting sandbox pods from unauthorized access.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: AuthManager type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `AuthManager` for RSA JWT authentication with thread-safe public key storage.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864332999,"end":1775864333017}}}}
