{"type":"text","timestamp":1775864431093,"sessionID":"ses_2863d152fffe0X4eNRN7W0rgq7","part":{"id":"prt_d79c49937001NZ4i70dHbQHBTP","messageID":"msg_d79c4766f001C7cufihznHhQaX","sessionID":"ses_2863d152fffe0X4eNRN7W0rgq7","type":"text","text":"Based on my analysis of AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Completed\n- **AuthManager implementation** (`pkg/picod/auth.go`):\n  - Thread-safe RSA public key storage with `sync.RWMutex`\n  - `PublicKeyEnvVar` constant (`\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`)\n  - `MaxBodySize` constant (32 MiB)\n  - `NewAuthManager()` constructor with env var loading\n  - `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` with PEM decode + PKIX validation (rejects PKCS#1)\n  - `AuthMiddleware()` Gin middleware with:\n    - Bearer token extraction and validation\n    - RS256 signing method validation (HS256 attack prevention)\n    - JWT claim validation (exp required, iat required, 1-min leeway)\n    - Error classification (expired, invalid signature, invalid signing method)\n    - Request body size limiting via `http.MaxBytesReader`\n  - `SetPublicKey()` / `GetPublicKey()` for runtime key rotation\n\n- **Server integration** (`pkg/picod/server.go`):\n  - AuthManager field in Server struct\n  - Middleware registration on `/api/*` routes\n  - `/health` endpoint bypasses auth middleware\n\n- **Test coverage** (`pkg/picod/auth_test.go` + `picod_test.go`):\n  - 85.5% test coverage (exceeds 80% requirement)\n  - All tests pass with race detector\n  - Tests for: missing header, invalid format, expired token, HS256 rejection, invalid signature, key rotation, PEM validation, concurrent access, leeway tolerance\n  - `go vet` passes clean\n\n### Deferred (Out of Scope)\n- JWT token issuance (Router responsibility)\n- Private key management\n- JWT refresh token handling\n- Token revocation/blacklist\n- Multi-issuer validation\n- Audience claim validation\n- Role-based access control within tokens\n- Rate limiting per token\n- Token introspection endpoints\n\n**Status**: Implementation complete, tests passing, ready for production use. Deferred items intentionally excluded as they belong to other components (Router) or future enhancements.","time":{"start":1775864431089,"end":1775864431089}}}
